At the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing, Federer was again the top seed and favorite, but lost in the quarterfinals to James Blake.[265] However, he found more success on the doubles court, capturing the gold medal in men's doubles with compatriot Stan Wawrinka, defeating Simon Aspelin and Thomas Johansson of Sweden.[266] At both the Athens and Beijing Olympic Games, Federer was the flagbearer for Switzerland in the opening ceremony.[267]
